Polyurethane dispersions are segmented based on type, application, and end-use industry. Under types, the market is divided into water-based polyurethane dispersions and solvent-based polyurethane dispersions. Water-based variants are further preferred due to their eco-friendly nature and low VOC content, making them suitable for various applications like coatings, adhesives, synthetic leather production, fiber finishing, and more. In comparison, solvent-based Polyurethane dispersions offer better durability and chemical resistance. In terms of applications, polyurethane dispersions find usage in coatings, adhesives, synthetic leather production, fiber finishing, and other sectors. The end-use industries for polyurethane dispersions include textile & leather, automotive, packaging, paints & coatings, and various others.

